On ftp.microsoft.com in the deskaps hierarchy there is a file called 
ia.exe.  Download this, it's a self extracting archive containing 
Internet Assistant.  I used it, but the WWW browser is worthless.  It is 
monumentally slow compared to Netscape for instance.  The HTML page 
writer may of some use to you (if you are very familiar with Word) but I 
have seen better HTML editors for Windows than what Microsoft has.  
Though it's still a Beta version, I give it a general thumbs down.



