From: chadster@stat.Berkeley.EDU (Chad Heilig)
Newsgroups: comp.os.ms-windows.apps.word-proc
Subject: Internet Asst. WYSIWYG bug (winword.opt)
Date: 27 Mar 1995 20:05:52 GMT
Organization: Statistics Dept., U. C. Berkeley
Message-ID: <3l75r0$k8j@agate.berkeley.edu>

I've noticed a peculiar `bug' in the Internet Assistant.  I've notified
Microsoft, but figured I'd share the news here, too.

I am running Word 6.0c on a 90-MHz, 8MB system, under Windows for
Workgroups 3.11.  I have a file with newspaper-style columns, say doc1.doc.
Before installing IA, the column width is WYSIWYG in Normal View and Page
Layout View.  After installing IA, everything is still fine, until I change
to Browse Web view.  Then I lose WYSIWYG on the columns (in Normal but not
Page Layout View).  When I revert to non-Web-Browse, the WYSIWYG is not
restored to Normal Wiew.  Finally, when I exit Word, rename winword.opt to
something else, restart Word, and reload doc1.doc, everything is WYSIWYG
again, until I enter Browse Web View.

The problem also applies to soft page breaks, and some line breaks not
associated with columns.

